  <figcaption class="ksdg-Figure-caption">

{{#markdown}}

- A Checkbox Group is a list of multiple items from which a user may select zero or more. Use when optional input is desired that allows for multiple selections from a small list.
- For groups with a large number of items (greater than 10&ndash;15 items), use subheaders to group similar options together and improve meaning.
- A Checkbox Group should never be a required field.
- A user should be allowed to select none of the items in the group.
- If the information must be collected, consider a different multi-select control.

{{/markdown}}

